  "prompt": "I am having problems with my friend. She is awesome, but she recently got a boyfriend. I just miss the way we once were. She's all over him and her other best friend. What should I do?",
  "response": "It's understandable to feel left out or nostalgic when a close friend enters a new relationship. Friendships can change during these times, but there are ways to navigate this situation thoughtfully:\n\n1. **Communicate Openly**: Consider talking to her about how you feel. Express your feelings without blaming her\u2014focus on how her new relationship has impacted your connection. Use \"I\" statements, such as \"I miss the time we used to spend together.\"\n\n2. **Be Supportive**: It\u2019s great that she has found someone she cares about, so try to be supportive of her new relationship. Acknowledging her happiness could strengthen your bond instead of creating distance.\n\n3. **Make Plans**: Suggest specific hangouts or activities that don\u2019t involve her boyfriend or her other friend. This can help rekindle your connection and remind her of the friendship you had.\n\n4. **Expand Your Circle**: Use this time to invest in other friendships or interests. This can help alleviate some of the feelings of loneliness while giving your friend space in her new relationship.\n\n5. **Give It Time**: Relationships often go through phases. As she settles into her relationship, she may find a balance between her romantic and platonic friendships.\n\n6. **Reflect on Your Feelings**: Sometimes, feelings of jealousy or loss stem from our own insecurities. Spend some time reflecting on what exactly is bothering you. \n\nNavigating friendships during changes can be challenging, but with open communication and a little patience, you can work through this phase together.",
